# Workspace workflow (Cursor harness)

Normative routing table: [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).

## Scope

- **Default:** Jira issue key as slug (e.g. `FLPATH-4164` → `flpath-4164`, `[a-z0-9-]+`).
- **No Jira ticket:** ask **"What scope ID should I assign to this workstream?"** before creating tracking artifacts.
- **One scope per stream** — list all submodules touched on the wiki entity page, not separate scope dirs per repo.

## Work tracking

| Artifact | Location |
| -------- | -------- |
| Durable facts, status, acceptance criteria | `wiki/entities/<scope>.md` (or `wiki/topics/`) |
| Optional execution plan | `.cursor/plans/<scope>.plan.md` |
| Submodule code | `submodules/<name>/` on a **task branch** ([submodule-git-workflow.mdc](submodule-git-workflow.mdc)) |

Do **not** create `pipelines/` or use `@rpi-status`.

## Verification (UI-modifying work)

1. Draft acceptance criteria on the entity page (or plan file); get human confirmation.
2. Run submodule checks and UI E2E per [wiki/topics/ui-verification-and-e2e.md](../../wiki/topics/ui-verification-and-e2e.md).
3. Record pass/fail and evidence on the **entity page**.

## Jira without a public repo

Paste self-contained conclusions in Jira; link wiki for checkout users — [wiki/workspace/jira-handoff-without-public-repo.md](../../wiki/workspace/jira-handoff-without-public-repo.md).

## Mission context

Per-submodule conventions: `constitutions/<name>/constitution.md`.
